notes.note:
Good evening, thank you for your previous email with the estimate for the timing cover gasket/seal replacement. Fortunately the timing cover gasket and seal are covered components under Heather's contract. Unfortunately we will not be able to include the replacement of the crank seal, intake manifold gaskets, water pump gaskets, valve cover gaskets and fluid exchanges as these are recommended items, and the fluids are not covered under this customer's contract. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees, shop supplies, and fluids, as well as a $100 deductible + tax. Additionally, our Mitchell Labour Guide lists the timing cover gasket replacement as 13.0 hours, so this will be the labour we will be authorizing for the claim. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$157.21
Labour-$1559.87 (13.0 hours x $119.99/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$210.22
Authorization-BILTVAKVX5

Total = $1827.30

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards,


Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
